    "Body": " Ripple is looking for a Communications Manager to join our fast-growing communications team. In this role, you will oversee the development and execution of communications in APAC; devise strategic, country-specific PR plans; manage regional PR agencies; and work with business partners and cross-functional teams within Ripple. This position will be based in Singapore. The ideal candidate is a skilled communications expert who has a successful track record of building a communications program from the ground up. You\u2019ll manage a diverse set of executives and spokespeople from different disciplines, including banking, fintech, blockchain and payments, and build narratives that these spokespeople can deliver during press interviews and at events. You thrive in a world where you are strategic but can also execute details flawlessly. You are creative with resources and energized by pushing the boundaries. No job is too big or small for you. Your peers admire and are inspired by you. And you never settle for the status quo. What You'll Do Lead communications and media strategy for APAC Draft and oversee the review process for press releases, talking points, messaging documents and other internal and external communications, seeing each through to completion. Interact directly with Ripple\u2019s leaders, top tier customers and industry influencers. Identify and counter misinformation that might interfere with our business and ability to serve our customers. Support media training for company executives, conduct spokesperson training prior to interviews and provide presentation support for speaking engagements. Manage external vendor and agency relationships. What We're Looking For 7+ years experience in public relations or product communications, ideally in both in-house and agency settings (tech experience preferred). Established relationships with media contacts and demonstrated success with media relations. Skilled at planning, prioritizing and executing in a fast-paced environment with keen attention to detail. Outstanding verbal and written communication with a special knack for telling stories in a clear, intriguing and effective way. Ability to draft focused messaging and content for press-related materials like press releases, executive briefing documents, press kits, and blog posts. Seeks opportunities to add value and contribute to the team\u2019s broader success. Excellent at project management that requires collaborating with many contributors. What We Offer The chance to work in a fast-paced start-up environment with experienced industry leaders A learning environment where you can dive deep into the latest technologies and make an impact Competitive salary and equity Medical and vision with 100% employer contributions for employees and dependents Generous wellness reimbursement program Weekly company-wide meeting - ask anything you may want to know Who We Are Ripple provides one frictionless experience to send money globally using the power of blockchain. By joining Ripple\u2019s growing, global network (RippleNet), financial institutions can process their customers\u2019 payments anywhere in the world instantly, reliably and cost-effectively. Banks and payment providers can use the digital asset XRP to further reduce their costs and access new markets. With offices in San Francisco, New York, London, Mumbai, Singapore, S?o Paulo, Reykjav?k, Washington D.C. and Dubai, Ripple has more than 300 customers around the world. Ripple is an Equal Opportunity Employer. We\u2019re committed to building a diverse and inclusive team. We do not discriminate against qualified employees or applicants because of race, color, religion, gender identity, sex, sexual preference, sexual identity, pregnancy, national origin, ancestry, citizenship, age, marital status, physical disability, mental disability, medical condition, military status, or any other characteristic protected by local law or ordinance. Please find our UK/EU applicant privacy notice here. ", 
